## Vendored / Derived Code

The BART/ subfolder derives from the BART R package (CRAN), authored by
Robert McCulloch, Rodney Sparapani, and Charles Spanbauer.  Its files are
licensed under GPL-2 and have been integrated here under that same license.

The LOGBART/ subfolder implements log-linear BART following Murray (2021,
JASA).  The original C++ tree code derives from BART (above); the log-linear
augmentation and Gibbs sampler logic are original to this project.

The GENBART/ subfolder implements RJMCMC-based generalized BART following
Linero (2022).  The hyperrectangle / cutpoint code derives from BART; the
RJMCMC machinery and likelihood interface are original.

The (forthcoming) SOFTBART_VENDOR/ subfolder will vendor the SoftBart R
package (Antonio R. Linero), licensed under GPL-2 or later.  See its
header files for the full attribution.

